##Wage arrears, layoffs, all-staff sales, competitive education radical self-help

Micro-signal, Rancaijing

A feature presentation, a daily in depth report, redefines the innovation economy.

Original by ran CAIJING

By Han Bing

Editor | Aalen

"Black Swan" out of the epidemic, corporate cash flow plummeted, many offline businesses face the test of survival, education institutions bear the brunt.

Recently, the Education Training Organization "Superior Education" was exposed to pay arrears, some employees were laid off. At the same time, staff feedback to the school district requires teachers to convert sales staff to sell classes, closed, and notice weekly classes not more than 20 hours, monthly sales less than 120 hours will be optimized or part-time.

According to employees, the company has had funding and operational problems since December 2019. There are on-the-job or off-the-job employees only received part of the salary after December, there are rumors of school closure, parents ask for refund phenomenon. In addition, some employees pointed out that the company has long been divided into two cards to pay salaries to avoid tax.

In response, yousheng education responded to Caijing by saying: "during the outbreak, the company tried its best to distribute wages in batches and will continue to replenish them in the future. Employees who can not keep up with the pace and requirements of the company will be optimized to a certain extent. During the outbreak, there may be irregularities in the process. Full sales is the method used by many companies, which is normal. "

Yousheng Education is an educational institution established for more than 20 years, focusing on personalized education in K12 field. There are more than 1500 stores in China with more than 13,000 employees. Chen Hao, the founder and chairman of Yousheng Education, is well-known in the industry. He was a guest of the BOSS Group on the job-hunting program "you're the one" .

Chen Hao also mentioned in a video program that winning education had listened to the advice of the consulting company, the results of a detour, leading to unreasonable expansion of the company, suffered major losses. The most miserable time, Chen Hao sold the house, mortgaged the car, returned home first to block the balcony door in order to prevent jumping off the building. Now, superior education is once again being tested.

Employees refer to outstanding education, wage arrears, redundancy

Require full sales

"On January 8, another colleague and I were working overtime, and the manager told us that you don't need to come tomorrow, just look for the finance, " Liao, a teacher at the Ergong campus of Yousheng Education in Guangzhou, told Cairen, "when asked why, HR said 'you were fired' because the probationary period was not up to par and did not comply with management. But I had already passed the probationary period for one month and had not yet signed the contract. "

Liao refused to apply for leave of his own accord. The supervisor removed him from all the work groups in the campus. Only 30 per cent of the end salary of December 2019 and January 2020 was paid, a few hundred dollars.

In a group of winners, nearly 170 employees claimed to have suffered from salary arrears, dismissal, forced transfer to part-time jobs, contract disputes and so on.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Outstanding Salary Information of employees in the winning education rights group

Screenshot from wechat group

According to Ms. Liao, her campus headquarters usually set the poverty line at 230,000(the cost of the campus) , with a total target of 460,000. Before the outbreak, their monthly revenue was around 230,000. In January, many students returned home for the winter vacation, fewer students, less than $100,000 in revenue. Moreover, she had heard that her school district was to be merged with another.

Screenshot of the winning educational notice / Photo provided by the respondent

Wang Ling, who has worked at Yousheng Education in Beijing's Jiulongshan district for more than two years, said she was fired and kicked out of her job group after the school district switched to online classes after the outbreak.

"I couldn't attend classes during the outbreak, which was force majeure, but I was required to attend the company's daily problem-solving and online meetings. I was going to wait for the situation to calm down and go back to the campus to get my computer before taking classes, but the head of my department asked me to leave my job on February 14 and switch to a part-time job on the grounds that I was not attending classes. I didn't agree, and on February 20 the head of the school and the head of the department removed me from all the groups. He still owes me more than 5,000 yuan in January and February,"Wang Ling said.

Teachers who were unable to attend classes due to the outbreak were fired for chatting

Photo / interviewee

There are many examples of "redundancy" . According to Deng Qiuyu, marketing officer and course consultant for the Shunyi District campus of Yousheng Education, who joined the company in July 2019, he was required to make 150 calls a day from home to sell classes during the outbreak, "On February 24, the principal told me that the company was not doing well and that I needed to optimize my staff so that I could write my own resignation letter for personal reasons so that I could rejoin the company when it opened offline. I didn't fill it out, and on the morning of February 25 the principal moved me out of all the work groups and now I can't punch in."

Some employees were underpaid and laid off. on-the-job employees reported that the current assessment mechanism for superior education is very strict. All teachers are required to switch to sales, and all teachers are required to sell classes.

The marketing advertisement of Youxin Education

The aggressive marketing of 20 hours a week and selling 120 hours of courses, or being forced to leave or switch to a part time job, has also drawn criticism from many teachers.

Koume, a teacher at Yousheng Education's Changsha Junior Palace campus, said: "In February, the campus started to switch to online classes, but many parents were reluctant to accept the transfer because the price was the same, the online courses were not effective, the school had online classes and parents did not want students to spend long hours staring at their mobile phones or computers. But the school district is asking us to convince parents that it's Ok for each teacher to cancel at least zero classes a month at first, then 10 or 20 hours a week, and now 20 hours a week, or be forced to leave or move part-time."

There are campus sales more radical means, the same day selling classes, the next day will be issued 10% of the total course price to the staff card, a daily wage, weekly salary and other incentive mechanisms.

"The school district also requires us to do marketing, selling 120 new classes a month to get paid. The school district says the more classes I sell, the faster I get paid, and so far I've had barely 20 classes, and none of the new ones have been sold,"Koume said.

On the issue of salary payment, on February 12, Yosemite issued a staff letter saying that the company had established rules for the payment of salaries to emergency employees in the short term under the epidemic, "A certain percentage of the salary will be paid on time, provided that the basic conditions of the employees are met, and compensation will begin in April for those who are not paid on time. Teachers will also get an extra incentive to teach online for more than 5 per cent of their jobs."

A 20-year-old institution

There have been contractual and operational disputes

Founded in 1999, the winner education group is the first of its kind in the education sector, Omo, which combines online teaching, central instruction and home-based tutoring to deliver a full-scale online-to-offline, campus-to-home education service, according to its website. There are more than 1,500 school districts with about 13,000 employees, and the schools are divided into three types: direct operation, agency management and franchise.

Ran CAIJING learned that prior to the outbreak, winning education began to show financial and operational problems.

Xiao Yu, the beijing-based brand content operator, left his job in December 2019, but has not yet been paid the more than 9,000 yuan he owes. Yangyang of the Tianjin Liuyuan campus also told Caijing, "We didn't get paid in January, and on or around January 20th there was a rumor that headquarters was going to give up on our campus, and parents came to refund our fees. Once a parent and the staff got into a big fight and the campus closed the next day. "

On Feb. 3, the campus had to open online. Later, Yangyang learned that she and several teachers who had taken a tough stance and demanded to be paid had all been "removed, " and that wechat groups and nails had been removed, owed her about 10,000 yuan in salary and several thousand yuan in medical insurance reimbursement.

In addition, several of the winning educators in the advocacy group said they were involved in social security and contract disputes.

Yusheng Education Jinsong School District Xiaoxue in 2019 in Yusheng Education Work for five months, after leaving the company found that she had not been social security, submitted to arbitration found his contract problems, "first of all, the party a of my contract is not the main company of Yousheng Education, Yousheng Guanghui Co. , Ltd. , but Beijing Hongzhi Shengwen Education Consulting Co. , Ltd. . Second, the contract shows that the probation period of six months is a part-time contract. The contract avoids the terms related to the probation period. The clause says that we work 24 hours a week, and the rest are all voluntary overtime, but in fact we work full-time. The part-time contract is actually a part-time contract and is not fully protected by the Labor Law. "

Xiaoxue also mentioned that, "The school district made our teachers work with the sales team, and I felt that the teachers were not in the class at all, but were trying to eliminate and sell the class by all means, " one person said. "The school district as a whole pays special attention to sales, and if you can get students there, you will get a bonus, and the teachers who take the class seriously will not be rewarded. "

There is also a phenomenon within the winning education called the "sub-card" . The company requires employees to register a family member or friend's salary card in addition to their own salary card, and the monthly salary is paid in two separate cards, "Say it's good for us, to avoid taxes. "

The winning Educational Work Group notifies the staff of the scorecard

In response to the problems reported by employees, Caijing called Yousheng Education headquarters customer service and city Manager for verification, the other side asked to leave contact, said will send a person in charge of contact.

Subsequently, a woman who claimed to be the winner of the Education Legal Affairs contacted Caijing to respond to some questions, during which she repeatedly "reminded" Caijing that what the employees said was neither objective nor comprehensive, and that they would be held liable if released without verification. The court said its response could be published after it had been confirmed, but added: "What I say today is for me alone. ". The main responses are as follows:

Regarding salary arrears: during the outbreak, the company was making every effort to issue salary in batches. In the future, the company may have to deal with the situation of three or four months with very little income. It is impossible to issue salary according to the original schedule. In the future, the company will issue additional salary gradually.

OPTIMIZATION PROBLEM: There may be a few exceptions, but thousands of employees are working with us. On the whole, the company hopes to retain as many comrades-in-arms as possible, so that more people break through their own. At the same time, during the outbreak can not keep up with the pace and requirements of the company, do not create value of employees, some optimization is legal and reasonable, the process may be irregular during the outbreak, these are difficult times and we expect the staff to cooperate as much as possible.

All Staff Sales: All staff sales is a method used by many companies, before the company mature, division of Labor does not require sales teachers, now adjust the business model requires all staff sales is normal.

CONTRACT ISSUES: We with the staff of the contract is full-time and part-time two, two in social welfare payment on the difference, the contract is very clear, the staff signed voluntarily, there is no problem.

The founder's appearance on a TV recruitment show was noted

Said he was so stressed he wanted to jump off a building

According to public records, the founder and chairman of Yousheng Education, Chen Hao, was born in 1978 with a master's degree in Beijing University of International Business and Economics and was born into a scholarly family. His father, Chen Chuanping, was a well-known mathematician in China, a researcher at the Chinese Academy of Sciences and a member of the professor, her mother, Tang Fangqiong, is a well known Chinese scientist and researcher at the professor. Chen Hao set foot in the field of education in 1999, researching the individualized education project for primary and middle school students.

Chen Hao used to be a member of the BOSS team on the show "you are the one" , often attacking job seekers on the show, and his sharp performance has attracted many people's attention.

Chen Hao appeared on the show "you're the one. "

At the same time, he has also shared his own entrepreneurial experiences, especially the lessons of failure, on the show Igor.

In 2007, he notes, Yousheng made nearly $20 million a year in profits, hiring consulting firms to continue to grow and learning from overseas chains, only to lose out. At that time several things were done, the first is to go to the middle, the 5-level management system of superior education was optimized off two levels, cut off nearly 1 / 3 about 500 people, "the whole structure is very floating, also broke the hearts of many employees, people are more lax. "

In addition, Yosemite has followed the advice of a consulting firm and adopted a core city approach in its national expansion, instead of focusing on a few major areas, resulting in an unreasonable talent ratio and an overall design bias. The following year the new store opened a large loss, headquarters subsidies thirty million, the third year is basically not open. In 2009, the company's money out clean, Chen Hao began to sell his house, mortgage car, in order to face the pain for a period of time, and then began to close shops stop losses.

"I used to take a taxi to the office and get off at the last stop to get to the office. I didn't want the staff to see that my car was gone. I have a temper when I'm stressed, and one time I smashed my computer with one punch. I was afraid of hurting people, and I told my assistant that I would close the door when I lost my temper, and that I would move out and live on my own for nine years because I didn't want to hurt my wife and kids when I got home. The most miserable time, I take a sofa to block the balcony door every day, worried about jumping off a building."Chen Hao recalls.

He admitted that he sometimes acts a bit gambling nature, feel that can afford to lose money as an important resource, there are some misconceptions. From the trough out, for a long time Chen Hao are conservative strategy, steady development, even if the company's operating data is very good will not quickly expand.

When the company recovered later, Chen Hao also made a lot of new projects and investments, "In 2012, when O2o was on fire, we launched an APP called 'teacher comes home' , which means that teachers go to class and spend $6.6 seven million a year. I lost one million in international education. My personal investment projects cost more than 200 million yuan, and some of them may be recovered."

Finally, he said, Entrepreneurial Road to continue to learn, to run small steps do not overreach, but also must pay attention to the team.

In 2019, the same 20-year-old education institutions, Weber English arrears of wages, closure and run away from the storm, the rights of parents, employees of the great momentum, caused widespread concern. Superior Education needs to guard against falling into a similar passive situation.

Under the epidemic, many enterprises business interruption, not only no income, but also as usual to bear the cost of rent, manpower, cash flow crisis hair-trigger. In order to survive, enterprises can only survive, active self-help, but in the process of cost reduction, downsizing personnel, and employees and customers frank and equal communication is very important. In compliance with the law and regulations, to strive for the understanding and cooperation of employees can reduce the risk of business failure. On the contrary, if do not communicate work is likely to backfire, accelerate death.

Success Education needs to be more empathetic and human in the way of self-help, and employees who suffer losses should fully understand the company's difficulties and actively negotiate solutions, according to the company. Times like these, we all need to get through them.

: : The title is drawn from the Web. Wang Ling, Xiao Yu, Koume, Yang Yang and Xiaoxue were given pseudonyms at the request of the interviewee.
